init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They have built walls in the sky to restrict where we can fly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We then decide to stop caring so much and drink heavily.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Then one day the United States is greeted with news that a new substance has been discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It gives us a sense of power and makes us feel like we are on top of the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They watch us destroy everything, even ourselves.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the United States is completely destroyed.
